📘 Complete Math Roadmap for Codeforces + ICPC
🟢 Tier 1 – Core Foundations
1. Number System
Priority: Representation (decimal, binary, octal, hexadecimal)

Divisibility rules, modular properties

Even/odd properties, remainders, digit sums

2. LCM & HCF
Priority: Euclidean algorithm

Prime factorization method

Applications in fractions, constraints

3. Algebra
Priority: Equations (linear, quadratic)

Inequalities, functions

Exponents, polynomials, factorization tricks

4. Logarithm
Priority: Properties (change of base, log rules)

Complexity analysis (log n)

Binary search depth, tree height problems

5. Permutation & Combination
Priority: nPr, nCr basics

Binomial theorem

Circular permutations, derangements

6. Probability
Priority: Classical probability

Conditional probability

Independent events, Bayes theorem basics

🟡 Tier 2 – Supportive Math
7. Sequence & Series
Priority: AP, GP formulas

Sum of n terms

Special series (squares, cubes), recurrence relations

8. Geometry
Priority: Angles, triangles, circles

Area formulas

Pythagoras theorem, cyclic quadrilaterals

9. Coordinate Geometry
Priority: Distance formula

Slope & line equations

Circle equation, intersection problems

10. Statistics
Priority: Mean, median, mode

Variance, standard deviation (basic)

🔵 Tier 3 – Contest Techniques
11. Modular Arithmetic
Priority: Modular addition/multiplication

Modular inverse

Fermat’s theorem, Chinese remainder theorem (basic)

12. Sieve of Eratosthenes
Priority: Prime generation

Complexity analysis

Segmented sieve

13. Prime Factorization
Priority: Trial division

Optimized factorization with sieve

Applications in divisors, LCM/HCF

14. Extended GCD
Priority: Euclidean algorithm

Extended version for coefficients

Applications in modular inverse

15. Binary Exponentiation
Priority: Fast exponentiation

Modular exponentiation

Matrix exponentiation (link to ICPC)

16. Combinatorics
Priority: nCr properties

Pascal’s triangle

Stars and bars, multinomial theorem

🟣 Extra Topics for ICPC (Beyond Codeforces)
17. Linear Algebra
Priority: Matrix operations

Determinants

Eigenvalues, matrix exponentiation

18. Set Theory & Logic
Priority: Sets & relations

Propositional logic

Boolean algebra basics

19. Inclusion–Exclusion Principle
Priority: 2‑set and 3‑set cases

General formula

Applications in counting

20. Advanced Combinatorics
Priority: Generating functions

Catalan numbers

Binomial identities, recurrence solving

21. Graph Theory Math
Priority: Adjacency matrix

Incidence matrix

Eigenvalues of graphs, spectral graph theory basics

22. Vector Geometry
Priority: Dot product

Cross product

Orientation tests, computational geometry

23. Discrete Probability & Expectation
Priority: Linearity of expectation

Variance

Random processes, distributions
